commit.message:
Fix `diff -y` "No newline at end of file" bug

If the last line of two files is the same, except one is missing
a trailing newline, diff -y uses '/' and '\' as separators:

```
  prompt% printf "same\nchanged\nlast"   > one
  prompt% printf "same\naltered\nlast\n" > two

  prompt% diff -y one two
  same                     same
  changed                | altered
  last                   \ last
```

Unfortunately, `colordiff` wasn't recognizing the '/' and '\' as
valid separators and consequently failed to color **ANY** lines.

PS: I should say, that's what GNU diffutils does, at least...

commit.message:
config: C:\ProgramData as /etc equiv. on Windows

On Windows, C:\ProgramData, set in the ALLUSERSPROFILE environment
variable functions similarly to the /etc directory on UNIX in modern
Windows versions.

Check for the first existing directory in the list '/etc',
$ENV{ALLUSERSPROFILE}, in that order, and use it as $etcdir.

Followup on 6e4c670 (Support config file on Windows., 2022-02-08).

Signed-off-by: Rafael Kitover <rkitover@gmail.com>

commit.message:
Support config file on Windows.

Use the env vars HOME, USERPROFILE for home location, in that order.

Use XDG_CONFIG_HOME, LOCALAPPDATA and APPDATA for user config dir
location, in that order.

Signed-off-by: Rafael Kitover <rkitover@gmail.com>

commit.message:
Accept --color=always and --color=never options.

For the --color option, accept "always" as an alias for "yes" and
"never" as an alias for "no", because GNU diff uses "always" and "never"
instead of "yes" and "no".  This allows colordiff to operate as expected
if used as a drop-in replacement for a GNU diff command line already
containing "--color=always", which is better than forcing the user to
change the option to "--color=yes".

Improve portability of Makefile

* Replace 'install' with INSTALL on platforms which don't have it or not in the
  expected form, e.g., HP-UX
* Don't perform chown because the syntax uid.gid isn't available  on some
  platforms and one shall not expect that it is root performing the installation
Provide support for 24-bit colour strings, thanks StephenWall
